1 2. The regulations adopted pursuant to subsection 1 must
2 require:
3 (a) Representative samples of each lot to be tested by a
4 cannabis independent testing laboratory;
5 (b) The collection of representative samples of a lot to be
6 conducted in accordance with standards established by the Board,
7 which must align with the most recent version of the ASTM
8 International Standard ASTM D8334/8334M, “Standard Practice
9 for Sampling of Cannabis/Hemp Post-Harvest Batches for
10 Laboratory Analyses”; and
11 (c) For each lot of cannabis flower, the total aggregate weight
12 of all representative samples to be collected for testing from the lot
13 to be:
14 (1) For a lot weighing less than 5 pounds, not less than 10
15 grams;
16 (2) For a lot weighing 5 pounds or more but less than 10
17 pounds, not less than 15 grams; and
18 (3) For a lot weighing 10 pounds or more but not more
19 than 15 pounds, not less than 20 grams.
20 3. As used in this section:
21 (a) “Harvest batch” means the useable flower and trim
22 contained within one or more specific lots of cannabis grown by a
23 cannabis cultivation facility from one or more seeds or cuttings of
